Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveVice President Yemi Osinbajo will be meeting members of the House of Representatives elected under the platform of the All Progressives Congress, APC on Wednesday.
The pastor invited the lawmakers to the Banquet Hall of the Presidential Villa for the breaking of the Ramadan fast (Iftar) on Wednesday.
A letter by the VP read by the Deputy Speaker of the House, Ahmed Wase, stated this on Tuesday.
Osinbajo declared for the 2023 presidential primary of the APC on Monday, and he hosted the party governors to Iftar on Sunday night to seek their support for his presidential ambition.
His declaration has been generating reactions across the country, considering the fact he would be contesting against his godfather and party national leader Bola Tinubu.
